dyn.desc: HP1_LP1_tC1_A1_Circuit_1_Alarm (R)(NL) reg: 31(NL)(NL)Description:(NL)HP1 - Circuit 1 alarm(NL)(NL)Value Meanings:(NL)0=Alarm OFF(NL)1=Alarm ON(NL) High pressure circuit 1(NL)The alarm is detected irrespective of the status of the pump and the compressors.(NL)The compressors corresponding to circuit 1 are immediately stopped (ignoring the set protection times), the buzzer(NL)and alarm relay are activated, and the display starts flashing.(NL)The fans corresponding to the condenser in circuit 1 are activated at maximum speed for 60 s, so as to(NL)oppose the alarm situation, after which they are switched OFF.
